head.title: An Exhortation Of The Churches of Bohemia To The Church of England

docTitle.titlePart: An Exhortation Of The Churches of Bohemia To The Church of England

Wherein is set forth The good of Unity, Order, Discipline and Obedience, in Churches rightly now, or to be Constituted. With A Description premised of the Order and Discipline used in the Churches of the Brethren of Bohemia. Written in Latin, and Dedicated to his Excellent Majesty Charles the Second, in Holland, at his Returning into England; If possible it may be for an Accommodation amongst the Churches of Christ

titlePage.docAuthor: By J. Amos Commenius, the onely surviving Bishop of the Remains of those Churches
titlePage.docImprint: London Printed for Thomas Parkhurst at the Three Crowns over-against the great Conduit, at the lower end of Cheap-side

condition.p: Vydání je vytištěno s chybou. Po straně 25 následují strany 30, 31, 23, 29, 26, 24, 32. Ve skutečnosti (podle toku textu) by měly strany následovat v tomto pořadí: 25, 26, 24, 23, 29, 30, 31.
